## Brand Identity

### Name

A good product name is:
- **Memorable**: Easy to recall
- **Pronounceable**: Can be said out loud
- **Spellable**: Users can type it correctly
- **Unique**: Searchable, no conflicts
- **Meaningful**: Connects to purpose (optional but helpful)

### Tagline

A tagline captures the essence in one line.

Structure: `[Benefit/Promise] + [Differentiator]`

Examples:
- "Your AI-powered journey to customized experiences"
- "Experience the web your way"

### Mission Statement

Template:
```
We [action] for [audience] by [method],
so they can [benefit].
```

### Values

3-5 core values that guide decisions:

| Value | Meaning | How It Shows |
|-------|---------|--------------|
| Value 1 | What it means | How it manifests |
| Value 2 | What it means | How it manifests |

## Visual Identity

### Logo

Logo types:
- **Wordmark**: Name in stylized text
- **Symbol**: Icon/graphic only
- **Combination**: Symbol + wordmark

Logo requirements:
- Works at small sizes (favicon)
- Works at large sizes (billboard)
- Works in single color (black/white)
- Has clear space rules
- Has minimum size rules

